      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why X Is the Most Exciting Tile in Scrabble</h2>
      <p>Drawing the X tile changes the game immediately. At 8 points, even a simple two-letter word like XI or XU scores 9 points — and on a triple-letter square, that jumps to 25 points for a single tile placement. X is the tile that creates those legendary 50+ point turns when it lands on premium squares with the right word.</p>
      <p>The challenge with X-starting words specifically is that they're less common in English. Most high-scoring X plays put X in the middle (TAXICAB, FOXHOUND) or end (WAX, BOX, FIX). But knowing X-starting words gives you options other players don't have — especially for opening moves and crossword formations.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Playing X-Words</h2>
      <p>X requires careful strategic thinking to maximise its 8-point value:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Target premium squares relentlessly:</strong> X on a double-letter = 16 pts. X on a triple-letter = 24 pts. Never waste X on a regular square unless you're scoring 20+ elsewhere in the word.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>XI and XU are your safety net:</strong> If no premium X-word fits, XI (9 pts) and XU (9 pts) are always available for parallel plays. They're short enough to fit anywhere.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Don't hold X too long:</strong> While it's tempting to wait for the perfect spot, holding X costs you rack flexibility. If you can score 15+ points with X, take it.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>XY- words for bonus combos:</strong> XYLEM, XYLOL, XYLITOL — the XY- opening uses the common Y tile alongside X for science-derived words opponents often don't know.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>End-game X is devastating:</strong> If your opponent is stuck with X at game end, they lose 8 points and you gain them. Conversely, never be the player holding X when tiles run out.</span></li>
      </ul>

